message.content:
Since the ten pairs of socks took 10 hours to dry under the same weather conditions, we can presume that one pair of socks also takes 1 hour to dry. 

If Tom has 7 pairs of socks to dry, it would take him 7 times the amount of time it takes to dry one pair.

Therefore, it will take Tom 7 hours to dry seven pairs of socks under the same weather conditions.
